A Pod is stuck in:
Pending

👉 Which component is MOST likely responsible?
👉 What would you check?

Solution:- 
Responsible Component:

# kube-scheduler

Because:
A Pod in Pending means → not assigned to any node yet

Debugging Steps (Production Order)
1️⃣ Check Events (MOST IMPORTANT)
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>

Look for:

• Insufficient CPU/memory
• 0/3 nodes available
• taints not tolerated

2️⃣ Check Nodes
kubectl get nodes
kubectl describe node <node-name>

 Look for:

• Resource pressure
• Node readiness

3️⃣ Check Scheduling Constraints

• NodeSelector
• Node Affinity
• Taints & Tolerations

4️⃣ Check Scheduler Health
kubectl get pods -n kube-system

# Golden Rule
Events tell you the truth faster than anything else
